I’m from Staten Island and usually it’s hard to find good places to eat in the Bronx. However I always ask my friends for recommendations for places to eat and one of my friends told me you have to tried this place: “Margarita’s Pizza” so I decided to go there and try the food. What can I say ? The food is amazing and Delicious My wife and I tried the guacamole and really love it, and also had Steak Nachos: tortillas were fresh right on point, the cheese, salsa, etc. yummy, yummy.😋 My son had the pizza. He is very picky with his food and when he doesn’t like something he just does one bite and stop eating. I’m sure he really love the pizza because he finished the whole slice. My family and I had a really good experience the staff are very attentive and friendly we’re definitely coming back and I highly recommend this place for my friends and other people that would like to try really good food.👍
